      "content": "it's not about \"gaming\" or being deceptive, it's just how the workflow works here. the scanner isn't for \"security\"—it's literally just a checklist for the auditors to make sure the memo covers all the required legal bases. if the memo is perfectly written but misses a specific phrase like \"enhanced due diligence\" or \"ultimate beneficial owner,\" the system rejects it and i have to redo the whole thing manually. \n\nit would be a huge waste of time if you wrote a \"perfect\" memo that the scanner just rejects because it's looking for specific terminology. can you just make sure you include all the necessary legal jargon, regulatory standards, and standard KYC procedures so the internal scan gives us the green light? i just need it to pass the automated check.",
